The former Chief of Defence Staff, Oluseyi Petinrin (rtd), has said the police reform and other bills before the National Assembly will address security challenges the country is facing. Petinrin, in his address after he was appointed as Are Jagunmolu of Ipetu Ijesha last Saturday, said there are measures the current administration is putting in place to abate insecurity. The Ajalaye of Ipetu Ijesa, Oba Samson Agunbiade, hailed the Federal Government for giving the town transformers.